🧪 LAB 1: Create VM without External IP + Private Google Access
✅ Task 1: Create VPC & Subnet (Enable Private Google Access)
Step 1: Go to VPC
Open Google Cloud Console
Navigate → VPC Network → VPC networks
Click Create VPC Network
Step 2: Configure VPC
Name: private-vpc
Subnet mode: Custom
Step 3: Create Subnet
Name: private-subnet
Region: (e.g.) us-central1
IP Range: 10.0.0.0/24

👉 IMPORTANT:

Enable ✅ Private Google Access

Click Done → Create

✅ Task 2: Create VM WITHOUT External IP
Step 4: Create VM
Go to Compute Engine → VM instances
Click Create Instance
Step 5: Configure VM
Name: vm-private
Region: same as subnet (us-central1)
Machine type: e2-medium
OS: Debian 12
Step 6: Networking (Important)
Click Networking
Select:
Network: private-vpc
Subnet: private-subnet
❌ External IP: Select None
Step 7: Create VM
Click Create
✅ Result
VM created without external IP
Can access Google APIs securely via Private Google Access
🎯 Key Concept

👉 Private Google Access allows VM (no external IP) to:

Access Google services (Cloud Storage, APIs)
Without using internet/public IP


🧪 LAB 2: Working with Virtual Machines (Minecraft Server)
✅ Task 1: Create VM with Extra Disk
Step 1: Create VM
Go to Compute Engine → VM instances
Click Create Instance
Step 2: Configure VM
Name: mc-server
Machine type: e2-medium
OS: Debian 12
Step 3: Add Disk
Click Add new disk
Name: minecraft-disk
Type: SSD
Size: 50 GB
Click Save
Step 4: Networking
Add Network tag: minecraft-server
Reserve Static External IP
Step 5: Create VM
✅ Task 2: Format & Mount Disk

SSH into VM:

sudo mkdir -p /home/minecraft

Format disk:

sudo mkfs.ext4 -F /dev/disk/by-id/google-minecraft-disk

Mount disk:

sudo mount /dev/disk/by-id/google-minecraft-disk /home/minecraft
✅ Task 3: Install Minecraft Server
Step 6: Install Java
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y default-jre-headless
Step 7: Download Server
cd /home/minecraft
sudo apt-get install wget
sudo wget https://launcher.mojang.com/v1/objects/.../server.jar
Step 8: Start Server
sudo java -Xmx1024M -Xms1024M -jar server.jar nogui
Step 9: Accept EULA
sudo nano eula.txt

Change:

eula=false → eula=true
✅ Task 4: Run Server in Background
Step 10: Install Screen
sudo apt-get install -y screen
Step 11: Run Server
sudo screen -S mcs java -Xmx1024M -Xms1024M -jar server.jar nogui

Detach:

Ctrl + A + D
✅ Task 5: Allow Game Traffic
Step 12: Create Firewall Rule
Go to VPC → Firewall
Click Create Rule

Config:

Name: minecraft-rule
Target: minecraft-server
Source: 0.0.0.0/0
Port: tcp:25565

Click Create

✅ Task 6: Backup Setup
Step 13: Create Bucket
export YOUR_BUCKET_NAME=your-unique-name
gcloud storage buckets create gs://$YOUR_BUCKET_NAME-minecraft-backup
Step 14: Create Backup Script
sudo nano /home/minecraft/backup.sh

Paste:

#!/bin/bash
/usr/bin/gcloud storage cp -R /home/minecraft/world gs://$YOUR_BUCKET_NAME-minecraft-backup/

Make executable:

sudo chmod 755 /home/minecraft/backup.sh
Step 15: Schedule Cron Job
sudo crontab -e

Add:

0 */4 * * * /home/minecraft/backup.sh
✅ Task 7: Stop Server
sudo screen -r -X stuff '/stop\n'

Then:

Go to VM → Click Stop
